-- 
Real IRA Claims Santander Bank Bomb in Derry, Irish News Reports

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-05-23T06:31:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/real-ira-claims-santander-bank-bomb-in-derry-irish-news-reports.html
The Real  Irish Republican Army 
claimed responsibility for a May 21 bombing of a branch of  Banco
Santander SA (SAN)  in Derry, Northern Ireland, the  Irish News 
reported.  The group telephoned the Belfast-based newspaper and using
a recognized codeword claimed responsibility for the attack, the
Irish News said.  The two kilogram (4.4 pound) bomb was placed in the bank by
three masked men and exploded shortly afterwards causing
extensive damage, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colm Heatley in Belfast at 
 cheatley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge in London at 
 Ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  